'''Stick in the mud''' is an [[idiom]] used to describe a person who does not want to participate in activities suggested by one or more people, usually because he  or she believes his or her [[idea]] is better, yet ignored, or because he or she believes the activity is not wholly [[kosher]].

More generally, one who is slow, old-fashioned, or unprogressive; an [[old fogey]].

